title: High-school football roundup | Koenig's four interceptions spark Alder
text:
Saturday October 10, 2015 6:28 AM 
Jonathan Alder 35, Marion Harding 14 
Andrew Koenig had four interceptions, three leading to touchdowns, to help host Jonathan Alder (6-1, 4-0) break free from Marion Harding (2-5, 2-2) in a Mid-Ohio Athletic Conference Red Division game on Friday night. With the Pioneers trailing 14-13 in the third quarter, Koenig returned an interception 75 yards to Harding’s 23-yard line to set up Trey Pugh’s 20-yard TD catch. Pugh finished with seven receptions for 145 yards. Austin Fooce scored Alder’s final two TDs from 1 yard and 32 yards, respectively. Both scores were set up by Koenig interceptions. 
>> High-school football results, box scores from Week 7 
Licking Valley 45, Granville 0 
Ethan Fout had 103 yards rushing on nine carries and scored three consecutive touchdowns to help Licking Valley (5-2, 2-0) shut out visiting Granville (4-3, 0-1) in the LCL Buckeye. 
Watkins Memorial 59, Lakewood 21 
Westley Brandon threw three first-half touchdowns, and Watkins Memorial (6-2, 2-1) routed visiting Lakewood (1-6, 0-3) in the LCL Buckeye. Brandon, who completed 12 of 14 passes for 218 yards, added a 96 yards rushing, including a 38-yard TD run early in the third quarter. Alex Miles led the Warriors with five receptions for 112 yards and two touchdowns. 
Utica 21, Heath 15 
Tony Hoover and Pierce Piazza each rushed for more than 100 yards and scored TDs, and Utica (2-4, 1-0) held off a late surge to defeat host Heath (4-3, 0-2) in the LCL Cardinal. 
Hoover scored on an 80-yard run, and Piazza scored the winning touchdown on a 4-yard run. Brad Potes scored on a 1-yard run for Utica, which gained all of its 282 yards on the ground. 
Aaron Latiolais completed 16 of 33 passes for 229 yards and a TD for Heath. 
DeSales 42, Warrensville Heights 7 
Dylan Todd rushed for two TDs and threw for a score in the second quarter, and DeSales (6-1) jumped to a 35-0 lead and cruised past visiting Warrensville Heights (3-4) in nonleague action. 
Todd scored on runs of 15 and 12 yards and threw a 28-yard TD to Joe Arnold. Alonzo Booth rushed for 90 yards and scored a 31-yard TD for the Stallions, who had four interceptions.
